\nIf society doesn't return to critically analyzing what we can do with what we already have, we'll continue marching on to a future of waste and obsoletion.  Landfills will continue to rise to and beyond their capacities, and 'optimized' and 'improved' production will drive the inflation of basic materials skyward, further breaching the wage gaps that already divide the citizenry.  Humans are already obsolete themselves in terms of production, we're being replaced by robots and automation under certain circumstances.  We haven't been entirely replaced yet because we can adapt, but how long will that last?
